<section id="license">
	<title>License</title>
	<indexterm><primary>license</primary></indexterm>
	<para>
		Until you purchase a license for <application>PhotoPulse</application>, it will operate in trial mode.
		When in trial mode, the shows you create are limited to five unique photos
		and contain a logo reminding you this show was created in trial mode.
		Also <application>PhotoPulse</application> displays a reminder dialog each time you start it.
	</para>
	<para>
		When you purchase a license, you must enter it into <application>PhotoPulse</application> to enable full functionality.
		Choose <guimenuitem>Enter License Key...</guimenuitem> from the <guimenu>Help</guimenu>
		to display the <guilabel>License Dialog</guilabel>.
		<mediaobject>
			<caption><para>License Dialog</para></caption>
			<imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/licenseDialog.png"/></imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
		<variablelist>
			<varlistentry><term>Key<indexterm><primary>license key</primary></indexterm></term>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Enter your full license key in this text area.
						You can right click on this are to display a menu allowing you
						to paste the key from the clipboard if you copied it from another application
						(e.g. email).
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term>
 					Paste
					<inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/licensePaste.png"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject>
				</term>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Click this toolbutton to paste from the clipboard.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term>
 					Clear
					<inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/licenseClear.png"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject>
				</term>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Click this toolbutton to clear the license text area if you made a mistake.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
		</variablelist>
	</para>
</section>
